Package: clawboot
Version: 1.2.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: arm64
Maintainer: Imran Duratbegovic <imranduratbegovicc@gmail.com>
Depends: sudo, systemd, libc6, libstdc++6, libgcc-s1
Description: Root-equivalent OpenClaw assistant setup for Raspberry Pi 5
 ClawBoot installs OpenClaw, a local Qwen 3.5 2B or 4B model, and optional
 Telegram or WhatsApp messaging through a simple desktop wizard.
 Installing this package grants the OpenClaw service account passwordless
 root access so it can operate the whole Raspberry Pi.
 The package bundles its application and browser-facing runtime and does not
 require optional GTK, WebKit, Python, or development packages.
